original: Eriksson, Nids Gunnar, fönste tra-fikinspek-tör, Göteborg, f. 30/11/89 i Jönköp. av Nils Magnus E. o. Ulrika Eriksson. G. 16 m. Elsa Edelfeldt. Barn: Lennart f. 17, Bengt 21. — Lä- rov :stud. Anst. v. SJ, stat :skriv, 14, förste |Stat :!skriv. 33, byråassist. 36, trafikinsp. 42, förste trafikinsp. 44.
translated: Eriksson, Nids Gunnar was born on November 30, 1889 in Jönköping. His parents were Nils Magnus E. and Ulrika Eriksson. He worked as a window traffic inspector in Gothenburg. He married Elsa Edelfeldt in 1916 and had two children, Lennart born in 1917 and Bengt born in 1921. He studied at the Vocational School of the Swedish State Railways, and then worked as a state clerk in 1914, first state clerk in 1933, bureau assistant in 1936, traffic inspector in 1942, and first traffic inspector in 1944.
